Package: CspStandSegmentation
Type: Package
Title: Comparative Shortest Path Forest Stand Segmentation from LiDAR Data
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
  person("Julian", "Frey", email = "julian.frey@wwd.uni-freiburg.de", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7895-702X")),
  person("Zoe", "Schindler", email = "zoe.schindler@wwd.uni-freiburg.de", role = c("ctb"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2972-1920"))
  )
Description: We provide functionality to segment single trees from a 
  forest stand scanned with proximate (e.g. terrestrial or mobile) laser scanning. 
  It strongly builds upon the lidR package. It provides the full workflow from a 
  raw point cloud to a full tabular forest inventory.  
URL: https://github.com/JulFrey/CspStandSegmentation
BugReports: https://github.com/JulFrey/CspStandSegmentation/issues
